ap:Text.PlainText: Edit Time Span dialog and filters
There are two main options for indexing of files - immediate and deferred. The options are set on a per-folder basis.
If a folder is set to immediate indexing, OmniaMea updates files in that folder immediately after they are changed, after new files are created in the folder and after files are deleted from it.
If a folder is set to deferred indexing, OmniaMea reindexes it only on startup.

If a folder is set to Excluded mode, it is not scanned. For example, if C:\yole is set to deferred indexing and C:\yole\private is set to excluded mode, OmniaMea indexes all files in C:\yole and its subfolders, except the files in C:\yole\private and its subfolders.
After a file is indexed, the Date property of the corresponding resource is set to the last modification date of the file. Thus, recently modified files appear in date-based views.
After a file is deleted from disk and OmniaMea rescans its containing folder, the file should be removed from the OmniaMea index.
If the option "Index hidden files" in the File Options pane is not set, files with the Hidden attribute set should not be indexed.
If the Access Control List permissions of the current user do not allow him to see the contents of certain folders, OmniaMea should handle this situation gracefully (with no crashing).
